  <a href="#1" id="1">
   A large study has shown that taking a single aspirin every other day could cut heart attack risk in half.
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   This was one of several reports
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   that show doctors can prevent heart attacks
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   as well as treat them.
  </a>
  <a href="#5" id="5">
   Doctor's also found
  </a>
  <a href="#6" id="6">
   that one aspirin and a single dose of clot dissolving given within 24 hours of heart attack dramatically cut the risk of a second fatal heart attack.
  </a>
  <a href="#7" id="7">
   Other researchers determined that some heart attack victims could be released from the hospital as soon as three days after their heart attacks.
  </a>
  <a href="#8" id="8">
   After 6 months, not one death was reported in the early discharge group.
  </a>
